# 11. みんなでライブ！

Miku: Hi, everyone! Thank you all for coming today!
Rin: We'll make sure our next show is even better! We hope you're looking forward to it!
Miku: The crowd sure was great today!
Rin: They sure were! I'm glad our new song and dance went off without any problems, too♪
Miku: Let's keep it up for our next—
Minori: Miku! Rin!
Miku: Hm? Minori?
Minori: That was a wonderful show! I had so much fun!
Rin: Hehehe. Thanks! Are you here by yourself today?
Airi: That was a really fun show, you two!  The third song felt especially powerful.
Shizuku: Yes. I always get so excited whenever I watch your performances.
Rin: Airi! Shizuku! You both came!
Minori: Yep! Haruka is here too.
Haruka: Thank you for the other day, Miku, Rin. Today's show was wonderful as well.
Miku: Hehehe. It makes me happy to hear you say that.
Airi: Thanks to you two, we were able to have more fun than we have in a while. I don't know if we can thank you enough.
Shizuku: I agree. It's been some time since I had so much fun singing up on stage.
Rin: I'm glad to hear it!
Miku: After seeing how happy you all looked while we sang that last song, the one born from your feelings, Rin and I were talking about wonderful the power of idols truly is.
Minori: Yeah! Idols really are the best, aren't they?!
Rin: Hey, since you're all here, why don't we put on another show together?
Haruka: Hehe. Sounds good. But before that, we have an announcement for the two of you.
Miku: An announcement?
Haruka: Yes. You see, the four of us have decided to team up and form our own idol group.
Miku: Oh, that's wonderful!
Miku: Your show was so wonderful! I'm glad I'll be able to see it again!
Shizuku: It makes us happy to hear you say so as well.
Rin: Have you decided on a group name?
Minori: Yep. We're going to be MORE MORE JUMP!
Minori: It's supposed to sound like we're all reaching out our hands, chasing our dreams of becoming idols, able to overcome any obstacles in our way.
Rin: I love it! It really suits you!
Airi: Right? We thought it sounded very optimistic, just like us.
Shizuku: I still like the sound of MORE MORE FIGHT, though.
Airi: Are you still going on about that?
Shizuku: Hehe. I'm just joking, Airi.
Airi: I wish your sense of humor wasn't so out there.
Rin: All right, then! Let's put on a show to celebrate the official formation of MORE MORE JUMP!
Airi: You just really want to perform, don't you?
Airi: Still, a celebration show sounds like fun!
Shizuku: Yes, it sure does. No reason to waste this opportunity to sing.
Minori: Yay! I can't believe I get to do another show with everyone so soon!
Minori: Oh, but are you going to be okay, Haruka?
Haruka: Thanks, Minori, but I'll be fine.
Haruka: Thanks to all your help, I've been able to move on. No matter what happens from now on, I'll be able to get on that stage.
Minori: Haruka!
Airi: Hehe. That's Haruka for you.
Shizuku: I feel like if the four of us are singing together, there's nothing to be afraid of.
Minori: Yeah, me too. It's a strange feeling.
Rin: Let's get ready for the show, everyone! Come on, Airi! Let's go!
Airi: R-Rin, hold on! Don't pull so hard! It's dangerous!
Haruka: Perhaps we should all follow them.
Minori: Yeah!
Shizuku: Yes, let's go.
Miku: Hehe. I'm so glad.
Miku: The smiles on their faces now that they've found their true feelings are so bright!
